The paper proposes a new algorithm for batch deep reinforcement learning, which falls under the umbrella of machine learning and artificial intelligence. The algorithm involves training a policy network using imitation learning, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) research. The paper also evaluates the algorithm's performance on the Mujoco benchmark, which is a standard benchmark in the field of reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper may also be relevant to researchers in computer vision (cs.CV) and control systems (cs.SY).
